This paper is likely to belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) category as it deals with inferring AS relationships based on BGP routing policies. It could also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category as the paper discusses special AS relationships that are relevant to a better understanding of Internet routing, which could have security implications. The paper also involves data analysis and mining, which could place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category. Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) as it deals with encoding and decoding BGP attributes. Finally, the paper could also belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) category as it discusses the importance of understanding AS relationships for Internet security.
